KATSINA – Dr Mustapha Muhammed Inuwa, the runner up at the just concluded All Progressive Congress (APC), Governorship primary election, has vowed to join forces with the party’s flagbearer to win the 2023 general elections in the state. Inuwa while addressing newsmen at his campaign office in Katsina at the weekend, said what had happened at the primary is an act of Allah. “When you pray for something, know that God knows the best thing for you. My task for now is to see to the success of the party at the forthcoming State Governorship election”. -Advertisement- “I am a party man. We have to work for the success of the party at the Governorship election and in other elections.” It would be recalled that the Katsina State APC held it’s Governorship primary on Thursday while the results were announced early Friday morning. Meanwhile, Dr Dikko Umar Radda, the State All Progressive Congress (APC) Governorship candidate in the 2023 election has paid a visit on Friday evening to his runner up at the primary, Dr. Mustapha Muhammed Inuwa to solicit for his support and understanding at the forthcoming State Governorship election. Radda who was elected early Friday morning at the party’s primary held in Katsina, visited Inuwa’s campaign office when he (Inuwa) was addressing the press and his supporters on the exercise. The APC Governorship candidate said “l came to see Inuwa to solicit his support as the party prepares for the state Governorship election”. POLL Radda said himself and Inuwa had come a long way since the era of Alhaji Umaru Musa Yaardua’s Government in the state. “I have come for your support as we prepare for the Governorship election and am confident, with your experience in politics, together insha Allah, we will deliver the state for our party”, he maintained.